<section class="hero-about">
  <p class="eyebrow">Our Story</p>
  <h1>Born from a refusal to <em>settle</em> for either</h1>
</section>

<section class="story-section">
  <p>LUMÉ began in a small lab in 2021, with a simple frustration: clean beauty meant weak formulas, and effective beauty meant compromising on what went into the bottle. We didn't believe that trade-off was necessary — we just hadn't seen anyone prove it wrong yet.</p>

  <p>So we spent eighteen months reformulating from scratch. Every ingredient had to clear two bars: it had to be traceable to a source we'd stand behind, and it had to work — not eventually, not theoretically, but visibly, on real skin, in weeks rather than months.</p>

  <div class="pull-quote">"Skin doesn't need more — it needs better."</div>

  <p>What emerged was a small collection, deliberately so. We make six products, not sixty. Each one earns its place through what it does, not what it claims. We test on real people before we test on paper, and we'd rather discontinue a product than dilute it.</p>

  <p>Today LUMÉ is made in small batches, packaged with intention, and used by people who've stopped asking beauty to be everything and started asking it to be honest.</p>
</section>

